@startuml sequence
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
' Diagrama de secuencia (UML) — configuracion, lazo de control (decision en OpenPLC) y monitoreo.
title Que hace el sistema

actor "Usuario (admin)" as U
participant "Frontend React" as FE
participant "Backend\nSpring Boot" as API
database "MongoDB" as DB
participant "Gateway Python\n(Raspberry Pi)" as GW
participant "OpenPLC\n(programa Ladder)" as PLC
participant "Relay + Cooler\n(GPIO14)" as HW

== 1) Configuracion de umbrales (con auditoria) ==
U -> FE : Define tempMin/Max, humMin/Max, histeresis, intervalo
FE -> API : POST /api/config
API -> DB : Guarda config activa (quien, email, cuando, IP)
API --> FE : 201 Created

== 2) Lazo de control (la decision vive en OpenPLC) ==
loop cada measurementIntervalSeconds (min 4 s)
  GW -> GW : Lee sensor DHT22 (pigpio, GPIO4)
  GW -> API : GET /api/config/latest
  API --> GW : Umbrales + histeresis + intervalo
  GW -> PLC : Modbus TCP: escribe HR0..HR5\n(temp, hum, umbralOFF, umbralON, humMin, humMax)
  PLC -> PLC : Histeresis + anti-ciclado (TON 15 s)\n+ fail-safe (banda invalida)
  GW -> PLC : Modbus TCP: lee coil 0 (cooler)\ny HR10 (palabra de estado)
  PLC --> GW : Decision del controlador
  GW -> HW : Acciona relay segun el coil\n(GPIO14, activo-alto)
  GW -> API : POST /api/measurements (temp, hum, coolerOn, status)
  API -> DB : Persiste la medicion (historial)
end

== 3) Monitoreo y auditoria ==
U -> FE : Abre dashboard / historial
FE -> API : GET /api/measurements, /api/config/history
API -> DB : Consulta
API --> FE : Datos
FE --> U : Estado actual, graficos e historial
@enduml
